nded on 15 December 1945.\n\n==Notable raids==\n* First \"thousand-bomber attack\" on [[Bombing of Cologne in World War II|Cologne]] on 30 May 1942 (shared)\n* [[Operation Chastise|\"Dambuster\" attack]] on the dams at the [[M\u00f6hne Reservoir]], the [[Edersee]] and [[Sorpe Dam|Sorpedam]] on 17 May 1943 (without backup)\n* [[Bombing of Braunschweig in World War II|Attack on Braunschweig]], 15 October 1944 (without backup)\n* Attack on [[Heilbronn]], 4 December 1944 (without backup)\n* Attack on [[Bombing of Dresden in World War II|Dresden]] on 13 February 1945 (without backup on the first attack)\n* [[Grand Slam bomb|Grand Slam attack]] on [[Hamm\u2013Minden railway#Schildesche viaduct|Schildesche viaduct]] near Bielefeld on 14 March 1945 (without backup)\n* Attack on [[Bombing of W\u00fcrzburg in World War II|W\u00fcrzburg, 16 March 1945]] (shared)\n* Attack on the oil refinery at [[T\u00f8nsberg]] in Southern [[Norway]], the last raid by heavy bombers of Bomber Command in World War II.\n\n==Commanders==\n'''1918 to 1919'''\n* 1 April 1918 [[Lieutenant Colonel]] [[Frederick Halahan]]\n* May 1918 [[Brigadier-General]] [[Charles Laverock Lambe]]\n\n'''1937 to 1945'''\n* 17 August 1937 [[Air Commodore]] [[William Bertram Callaway]]\n* 11 September 1939 [[Air Vice-Marshal]] [[Arthur Travers Harris]]\n* 22 November 1940 Air Vice-Marshal [[Norman Bottomley]]\n* 12 May 1941 Air Vice-Marshal [[John Slessor]]\n* 25 April 1942 Air Vice-Marshal [[Alec Coryton]]\n* 28 February 1943 Air Vice-Marshal [[Ralph Cochrane]]\n* 16 January 1945 Air Vice-Marshal [[Hugh Constantine]]<ref>{{harvnb|Moyes|1976|p=343.}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Royal Air Force groups]]\n\n==References==\n===Citations===\n{{Reflist|20em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last=Moyes |first=Philip J. R. |title=Bomber Squadrons of the RAF and Their Aircraft |location=London |publisher=Macdonald and Jane's |year=1976 |orig-year=1964 |edition=2nd |isbn=978-0-354-01027-6 |ref=harv}}\n